      of the question.Docetism was a theory which found its confirmation in narratives and 
      legends of certain psychic or spiritual powers ascribed to the "perfect 
      man."The christological and soteriological theories of the Gnostic 
      philosophers were not, as many would have us believe, invented altogether
      à priori; they rested, I hold, on the basis of a veritable 
